{
  "text": "Diagnosis of VL involved a clinical case definition (fever >2 weeks and splenomegaly), which was confirmed using the rK39 rapid diagnostic test (DiaMed-IT-Leish). For immunocompetent patients in India it is 98.8% and 97.6% sensitive and specific respectively [CITATION_1] ; its accuracy in immunocompromised patients had not yet been fully established although is likely to be lower. In cases of suspected relapse, or where there was high suspicion despite negative antibody detection tests, confirmation by splenic or bone marrow aspiration was performed.",
